data.name: Beef Tenderloin and Vegetable Skewers
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy beef tenderloin and colorful veggies grilled to perfection for a delightful meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: Soak wooden skewers in water for 30 minutes if using wooden skewers to prevent burning.
Cut the beef tenderloin into 1-inch cubes and set aside.
Chop the bell peppers, zucchini, and red onion into similar-sized pieces to ensure even cooking.
In a large bowl, combine the beef, bell peppers, zucchini, and onion.
Drizzle with olive oil and season with garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Toss to coat evenly.
Thread the beef and vegetables onto the skewers, alternating between them.
Preheat your grill or a grill pan over medium-high heat.
Cook the skewers for about 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally, until the beef is cooked to your desired doneness and the vegetables are tender.
Remove from grill and let rest for a few minutes before serving.
